description:
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust has a vacancy for a full-time (12 PA’s) Consultant Interventional Cardiologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join a team of 11 Cardiologists, with a variety of sub-speciality interests, working at Wexham Park Hospital and supporting patients across East Berkshire and parts of South Buckinghamshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department includes a 14 bedded Coronary Care Unit, Step Down Cardiology Ward, 2 Catheter Laboratories and Cardiology Investigations Unit. The Cardiology PPCI on-call commitment is 1:6 with a 1:16 commitment to an inpatient ‘Consultant of the Week’ rota when other duties are reduced.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be on the GMC specialist register or be within 6 months (from the date of interview) of their expected CCST date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Peter ClarksonJob titleClinical LeadEmail addresspeter.clarkson@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Gareth Roberts, Chief of Service, General Medicine &amp; Emergency Services on 01753-633000 gareth.roberts2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
